            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Yeah the workaround is to disable the recommended style, but I think it should be opt-in and not opt-out. Especially since this overwrites an explicit .editorconfig setting, it should be considered a bug. I think there might be some kind of race condition at some point where sometimes editorconfig wins and sometimes the recommended style.\n\nI can somehow agree that there is a default recommended style that is used as a fallback in case the user has set no preferences for formatting. But as soon as a format indication exists, in either vim config, .editorconfig or otherwise, the \"default fallback\" should be disabled.",
