            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "It's my first time trying to contribute, so I might be off the mark, but it looks to me that some plugin or something in @stevenroose 's configuration is forcing ftplugin to run again.\n\nAs far as I could understand, in the normal flow ftplugin runs first, but then EditorConfig runs and overwrites the settings, that's why it's adhered at the start. Then, at a later point something clears did_ftplugin (which might be legitimate) and ftplugin runs again.\n\nI don't know enough yet to see what's the good solution here, but a naive solution might be that EditorConfig needs to run whenever ftplugin is run (although maybe that has undesirable side effects, I don't know).\n\nFrom what I understood, I think this script should be a minimal reproduction:\n\n``` bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# Create a temporary directory and seed it with the required files\ntmpdir=\"$(mktemp -d)\"\ntrap 'rm -rf \"$tmpdir\"' EXIT\ncd \"$tmpdir\"\n\ncat > .editorconfig <<'EOF'\nroot = true\n\n[*.rs]\nindent_style = tab\nindent_size = 4\nEOF\n\ncat > main.rs <<'EOF'\nfn main() {\n    println!(\"hello\");\n}\nEOF\n\n# Trace what's running\necho \"Repro directory: $tmpdir\"\necho \"Neovim version: $(nvim --version | head -n 3)\"\necho -e \"Initial open, then force Rust ftplugin to run again by setting filetype again\\n\"\n\n# Open the file, check expandtab, shiftwidth and softtabstop\necho -e \"Open main.rs and check settings:\\n\"\nnvim --clean --headless main.rs \\\n  +'set verbose=1' \\\n  +'verbose set expandtab? shiftwidth? softtabstop?' \\\n  +qa\n\n# Open the file again, set the filetype to rust, and check expandtab, shiftwidth and softtabstop again \necho -e \"\\n\\nSet filetype=rust after the file is already open:\\n\"\nnvim --clean --headless main.rs \\\n  +'set verbose=1' \\\n  +'set filetype=rust' \\\n  +'verbose set expandtab? shiftwidth? softtabstop?' \\\n  +qa\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-06-06T19:58:11Z",
